      "text": [
        " رِوَايَةِ عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ بْنِ اَلْمُغِيرَةِ أَنَّهُ قَالَ: «لاَ بَأْسَ أَنْ يَعُدَّ اَلرَّجُلُ صَلاَتَهُ بِخَاتَمِهِ أَوْ بِحَصًى يَأْخُذُ بِيَدِهِ فَيَعُدُّ بِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.987 - In the narration of Abdullah ibn al-Mughira, it is said:\n\"There is no harm if a man counts his prayers using his ring or by using pebbles that he holds in his hand and counts with them.\""
        ]
      }
    },
